## Reference websites

### transporttrailersales.com

What to draw from: Clean inventory browsing experience, functional layout, industry-standard navigation (Products, Inventory, Rentals, Parts, Contact). The inventory page organization with filtering by trailer type is a strong model.

### docksidetrailers.com

What to draw from: Recently redesigned with a modern feel. Strong team page with personality. Manufacturer showcase pattern that could translate well to a “trailer types” or “brands we know” section. Clean visual hierarchy.

### breadnertrailers.com

What to draw from: Jason specifically loves the ongoing/rotating images on the homepage. Breadner uses strong hero imagery and scrolling visual elements that showcase active operations. Replicate this approach with a hero carousel or auto-scrolling image strip featuring yard shots, trailer inventory, and team at work.
